RE: Understanding Why Bad Things Happen to Good People People don't want to know cause and effect. They want to pity the ones stricken by harm and file it all away asap, before they have too many serious thoughts about it.
They thank the lord that it wasn't them and are done with it.
Science is the process we've designed to be responsible for generating our best guess as to what the fuck is going on. Girly Man
